      "file_path": "openecomp-be/lib/openecomp-sdc-validation-lib/openecomp-sdc-validation-core/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/validation/impl/validators/HeatValidator.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 158,
      "message": "You're getting properties twice here: once to check for null, and another to return. What if getProperties() were actually reading from disk? You would perform an expensive I/O operation twice. The right way is to get properties into a local variable. But you don't even need it here. Because resourcePropertiesValues = value.getProperties() will hold null if getProperties() returns null, and some value otherwise.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
